# Memory Access

**Location:** `~/.cursor/memory/` (local per machine, never tracked in dotfiles)

## Namespace-to-Directory Mapping

| Namespace | Directory |
|---|---|
| `org.global` | `org/global/` |
| `org.security` | `org/security/` |
| `project.<name>` | `projects/<name>/` |
| `project.<name>.<domain>` | `projects/<name>/<domain>/` |
| `project.junk` | `projects/junk/` |
| `session.current` | `session/current/` |

## Read Protocol

1. Determine relevant namespace(s) from task context
2. Check if directory exists — if not, no memory for that namespace
3. Read `_index.md`; scan table for matches by category, tags, keywords, status
4. Read individual `.md` files ONLY for matches; max 5 per query
5. If >5 matches, narrow filters or work from index summaries
6. Do NOT query `session/current/` unless explicitly looking for recent session context

## Write Operations

See `context-memory` skill for write protocol, entry schema, and index maintenance.

## Initialization

If `~/.cursor/memory/` doesn't exist, create it and target namespace directory before writing.

## Session Start

If `_pending_refresh.md` exists in any accessed namespace, process it before proceeding.
